{
  "texts": [
    "We assess how the algorithm performs when diversity is integrated as a key component of the fitness function compared to when it is excluded.",
    "The inclusion of diversity is hypothesized to prevent premature convergence on suboptimal solutions and encourage a more exhaustive exploration of the solution space.",
    "This comparative analysis helps us to understand the benefits and limitations of our approach under different testing environments and conditions, providing insights into its generalizability and effectiveness in adapting to various problem complexities.",
    "RQHow does our proposed RL-based approach work under different conditions?In addressing this question, we evaluate the performance of our RL algorithm across different experimental setups.",
    "Specifically, we contrast the outcomes when the reward structure is solely based on execution time against configurations where the reward includes both execution time and a diversity component."
  ]
}